The paper discusses a solution for parallel distributed logistic regression for vertical federated learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a parameter server architecture, which is commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper deals with decentralized data owned by different data providers, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the issue of data privacy and leakage, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the system, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
